34 trait Xmlable {
35   /**
36     * creates JsValue from this class
37     *
38     * @return JsValue
39     */
40   def toXml(): Node
41 }
42 
43 trait Jsonable {
44   /**
45     * creates JsValue from this class
46     *
47     * @return JsValue
48     */
49   def toJson(): JsValue
50 }
51 
52 trait JsonableCompanion[A] extends ClassnameLogger {
53   val reads: Reads[A]
54   val writes: Writes[A]
55   val format: Format[A] = Format(reads, writes)
56 
57   /**
58     * parse object from Json
59     *
60     * @param json
61     * @return Option if parsing error
62     */
63   def fromJson(json: JsValue): Option[A]
64 }

258 object MdMetadata extends ClassnameLogger with JsonableCompanion[MdMetadata] {
259 
260   override implicit val reads: Reads[MdMetadata] = (
261     (JsPath \ "fileIdentifier").read[String](Reads.filterNot[String](ValidationError("String empty"))(_.trim().isEmpty))
262       or Reads.pure(UUID.randomUUID().toString)
263       and
264       (JsPath \ "title").read[String] and
265       (JsPath \ "abstrakt").read[String] and
266       (JsPath \ "keywords").read[List[String]] and
267       (JsPath \ "topicCategoryCode").read[String] and
268       (JsPath \ "hierarchyLevelName").read[String] and
269       (JsPath \ "scale").read[String] and
270       (JsPath \ "extent").read[MdMetadataExtent] and
271       (JsPath \ "citation").read[MdMetadataCitation] and
272       (JsPath \ "lineageStatement").read[String] and
273       (JsPath \ "responsibleParty").read[MdMetadataResponsibleParty] and
274       (JsPath \ "distribution").read[MdMetadataDistribution]
275     ) (MdMetadata.apply _)
276 
277   override implicit val writes: Writes[MdMetadata] = (
278     (JsPath \ "fileIdentifier").write[String] and
279       (JsPath \ "title").write[String] and
280       (JsPath \ "abstrakt").write[String] and
281       (JsPath \ "keywords").write[List[String]] and
282       (JsPath \ "topicCategoryCode").write[String] and
283       (JsPath \ "hierarchyLevelName").write[String] and
284       (JsPath \ "scale").write[String] and
285       (JsPath \ "extent").write[MdMetadataExtent] and
286       (JsPath \ "citation").write[MdMetadataCitation] and
287       (JsPath \ "lineageStatement").write[String] and
288       (JsPath \ "responsibleParty").write[MdMetadataResponsibleParty] and
289       (JsPath \ "distribution").write[MdMetadataDistribution]
290     ) (unlift(MdMetadata.unapply))
291 
292   def fromJson(json: JsValue): Option[MdMetadata] = {
293     Json.fromJson[MdMetadata](json) match {
294       case JsSuccess(r: MdMetadata, path: JsPath) => Some(r)
295       case e: JsError => {
296         val lines = e.errors.map { tupleAction =>
297           val jsPath = tupleAction._1
298           val valErrors = tupleAction._2.map(valErr => valErr.message).toList.mkString(" ; ")
299           jsPath.toJsonString + " >> " + valErrors
300         }
301 
302         logger.error(s"JsError info  ${lines.mkString(" | ")}")
303         None
304       }
305     }
306   }
